         <div type="translation" xml:space="preserve"><head>Translation</head><p>Of M<ex>archius</ex> Nasif and M<ex>archia</ex> Mathlich, mother; the Marchii Nimira and Fydel, their sons, had this built for their dear parents.</p></div>
         <div type="commentary">
            <head>Commentary</head>
            <p>A photograph taken by flashlight by Mr. Michael Ballance in <date>1955</date> has made possible a more accurate reading of the text.</p>
            <p>M is for Marchius which appears in full in  <ref type="inscription">898</ref>. For the name Nimira, see also  <ref type="inscription">898</ref>: for Fydel, see <ref type="inscription">900</ref>.</p>
         </div>
